message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in Tonga in the past 20 years was the coronation of King George Tupou V in 2008. This event marked a significant transition for the country as it marked the passing of power from King Tupou IV, who had ruled for 41 years, to his successor. The coronation was a grand ceremony attended by dignitaries from around the world and included traditional rituals, symbolism, and celebrations that showcased Tonga's rich cultural heritage. This event symbolized continuity and stability for the country while also signifying a shift towards modernization and democratic reforms under King George Tupou V's leadership.
